     7	Q: Why do I need Partition Resizer?
     8	A: You don't. You can as well backup all your data, use FDISK to repartition
     9	your drive, and restore the backuped data in the new partition. But while
    10	this can take sometimes more than an hour, and this only if you have a tape
    11	streamer (don't even think about using floppy disks), Partition Resizer will
    12	do the job in 5-10 minutes in most cases. 
    13	
    14	Q: Where can I find the latest version of Partition Resizer?
    15	A: It can always be found in any SimTel mirror site, like oak.oakland.edu,
    16	or nic.funet.fi, in the directory SimTel/msdos/diskutil under the name 
    17	presz???.zip. ??? is the current version number.
